  "body": "I have a simple task to solve:\n\n```\n[13:02] <MetaZoffix> m: say \"7\\x[308]\" ~~ /^ \\d+ $/\n[13:02] <+camelia> rakudo-moar f0bb58: OUTPUT«｢7̈｣␤»\n[13:03] <MetaZoffix> Is there an easy way to make it look for *just* numbers without combiners?\n```\n\nBut I'm not seeing any section on this in https://docs.perl6.org/language.html\n\nBy osmosis, I know I need some sort of [.NFD](https://docs.perl6.org/type/NFD) or something along the lines of that, but from a perspective of someone who's not familiar with what unicode forms there are and what they're all about, it's hard to understand what I am supposed to do to make my original operation work right.\n\nThere should be a page that explains all of this stuff.\n",
